text: I see here Silent Hill, Barker (Hellreiser, Book of blood), Poe, Mama, Alice, fairytales etc. Which is fine. But this one looks like every other new film regarding the picture: all that CGI, blurry, fake (sky, background, characters). Why do all movies of this sort have to look like that? Even Deltoro himself can't seem to do any better now. The same goes for Tim Burton (remember how Sweeny Todd looks? or this-more-recent-horror-comedy-with-johnny-depp whatever it was called), and Tarsem Singh. I know I've seen, but right now I even struggle to recall new horror films with real, clear picture besides "Let the Right One in". I'm not saying the background and costumes should be minimalistic or something. But they should be clear and without or with less CGi all around.
